transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling the system.

Speaker 2: Thank you for calling the system.

Speaker 1: Yes, how are you doing? I bought some blue pills.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: And when I get up in here, when I get on there, it says generic Viagra.

Speaker 2: Now, when I was online, it didn't say nothing about it.

Speaker 1: It was generic Viagra, and it had some VC.

Speaker 2: AGV.

Speaker 1: Huh?

Speaker 2: AGV.

Speaker 1: AGV?

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I can help you, sir. I need your name.

Speaker 1: James Taylor.

Speaker 2: Zip code 60652.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: I see your order here.

Speaker 2: Can you tell me what it stands for?

Speaker 1: AC339.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: So we did screw up, sir.

Speaker 2: I'm going to get this fixed.

Speaker 1: The AGV pill, what does your name say on it?

Speaker 2: Yeah, that's what I was saying.

Speaker 1: That's what I was saying on the thing, and I'm looking at this, and then it said generic Viagra,

Speaker 2: and I didn't think that y'all – I didn't know y'all do generic,

Speaker 1: because I didn't really want any generic Viagra.

Speaker 2: I thought, you know –

Speaker 1: Yeah, we sell both kinds, but I'm getting you the AGV,

Speaker 2: so what you have there is that you can throw it away,

Speaker 1: and you're going to get a new order up again.

Speaker 2: Well, I mean, I paid for them already, though, so.

Speaker 1: No, no, I know.

Speaker 2: Sometimes people get worried if we have to re-charge them,

Speaker 1: and they have to re-charge them every time.

Speaker 2: I just have to make it clear you're not being charged again.

Speaker 1: Yeah, because don't the AGVs,

Speaker 2: ain't they supposed to be better than just the generic Viagra?

Speaker 1: They are, so I'm not saying that we won't get you those.

Speaker 2: Okay, so you have any inclination when you –

Speaker 1: I guess it took two or three days or something, so I guess –

Speaker 2: Yeah, it's just about tomorrow.

Speaker 1: Okay, and that's for sure?

Speaker 2: Yes, I just –

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you, sir. I appreciate that.

Speaker 2: Of course, James. Have a good day.

Speaker 1: You too.
